The same table of the data for piercings.
The column headings are "Pierced," "Not Pierced," and "Total." The
Rows are "Male," "Female," and "Total." The data in the cells is
given in "Row, Column:
    Value" format:
    Male, Pierced: 36;
    Male, Not Pierced: 144;
    Male, Total: 180;
    Female, Pierced: 288;
    Female, Not Pierced: 32;
    Female, Total: 320;
    Total, Pierced: 324;
    Total, Not Pierced: 176;
    Total, Total: 500;
    In this table, the first row (Male) has been highlighted. The {Male, Pierced: 36} cell is
in dark green, and the rest is in light green, showing that we can use this row to calculate
the conditional probability.

